Its actually simple. Its the ***Longest Uncommon Subsequence***. 

***Longest*** - The longest is when you consider the entire string's length. 
***Uncommon*** - Even if one char is out of place its uncommon.
***Subsequence*** - the entire string is also a sub-sequence right?

So if its same string then return -1, else return length of the longest string.

``` 
int findLUSlength(string a, string b) {
        if(a==b)
            return -1;
        return max(a.size(),b.size()); 
    }
