<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
If both the string is equal then there is no longest subsequences.
else return the string length which is longer than other.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int findLUSlength(string a, string b) {
        if(a.size()!= b.size()){
            return max(a.size(),b.size());
        }
        if(a != b){
            return a.size();
        }

        return -1;
    }
};
```

