# Intuition
Just try to figure out cases where we can get -1. After a few examples we will notice, that common sequence is possible only in cases when a is subsequence of b or b is subsequence of a. But if we have "aaa" & "a" for example - the answer will be 3, so the only case we get a -1 is an equivalence of strings.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: **O(1)**
- Space complexity: **O(1)**

# Code
```
import kotlin.math.max

class Solution {
    fun findLUSlength(a: String, b: String): Int {
        if (a == b) return -1
        return max(a.length, b.length)
    }
}
```

